SA Express has confirmed that it has cancelled its flights for operational reasons. The company says it has informed affected passengers and made alternative arrangements for them. However, the company’s spokesperson, Mpho Majatladi, says normal operations are expected to resume on Thursday. “The airline made all the efforts to accommodate the passengers to ensure that they are able to travel to and from their destinations. What the airline also did was to ensure that staff at all the airports are available to assist the passengers. As an airline we apologise for the delays and cancellations that happened today (Wednesday). “